Low-cost interventions for heat stress mitigation in urban informal settlements
                    Yu Qian Ang 
            ORCID: orcid.org/0000-0002-9757-606X1,  Sparsh1, Tao Wang 
            ORCID: orcid.org/0009-0001-2845-48351,2 & …Lup Wai Chew 
            ORCID: orcid.org/0000-0003-2225-10571 Show authors

Nature Cities

(2026)Cite this article

Subjects

            Climate changeDeveloping worldEnvironmental studiesSociety

AbstractUrban informal settlements face severe heat stress yet lack affordable cooling solutions. We engage two communities in Bihar, India, to test two low-cost, rapidly deployable interventions. Using over 2 million minute-level temperature observations, we find both interventions improve thermal comfort in informal dwellings: radiant foils lower indoor temperatures by 1.24 °C, whereas Mylar blankets achieve a reduction of 0.97 °C. These findings demonstrate a scalable strategy for climate adaptation in vulnerable urban communities.

